race.comment: Weak race and expecting HIGH TEMPO (11) to be the big improver. Last time in quick went to the mile and got off the mark before a moderate run in tougher grade then spelled. Was well in the market fresh over 1400m but blew the start so the run was much better than it looked. Fitter and extra trip a plus. One of the few in the race with good upside and looks nicely placed to return to winning form. NORWOODS (2) is coming off a poor run and appeals as a danger. Last two have been in tougher and did win only try course and distance. Willing to give another chance. BEARBRASSBLACKFISH (9) should be ready to show best after two runs back and the extra ground looks a plus. BOB THE HORSE (3) is better than latest over a bit further. Has placed 3/3 this curse and distance so gets chance to find best. TRINITY'S D'ORO (7) has good speed and will take catching despite a tricky gate.
